1
00:00:02,461 --> 00:00:07,299
ARCHER: CAPTAIN'S PERSONAL LOG,
FEBRUARY 12, 2152.

2
00:00:07,341 --> 00:00:10,093
AFTER A BRIEF DETOUR,
WE'RE BACK ON COURSE FOR RISA.

3
00:00:10,135 --> 00:00:13,180
EVERYONE'S LOOKING FORWARD TO
SOME MUCH NEEDED SHORE LEAVE.

4
00:00:13,221 --> 00:00:16,767
I'VE GOT MY EYE ON A PLACE
CALLED SURAYA BAY.

5
00:00:16,809 --> 00:00:19,353
VILLAS BUILT
RIGHT INTO THE CLIFFS.

6
00:00:19,394 --> 00:00:23,315
A PERFECT SPOT TO ENJOY
A FEW GOOD BOOKS.

7
00:00:23,357 --> 00:00:25,275
MIGHT EVEN DO A LITTLE DIVING
WHEN I --

8
00:00:25,317 --> 00:00:27,235
[ BEEPS ]

9
00:00:27,277 --> 00:00:29,530
COMPUTER, PAUSE.

10
00:00:29,571 --> 00:00:30,948
ARCHER.

11
00:00:30,990 --> 00:00:32,992
We're picking up
a distress call, Captain.

12
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:34,242
It's coming from a vessel

13
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:36,244
approximately
two light-years to port.

14
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:37,496
ANY IDEA WHO IT IS?

15
00:00:37,538 --> 00:00:40,708
No, sir.
Should we alter course?

16
00:00:42,334 --> 00:00:45,629
GO AHEAD.
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

17
00:00:47,548 --> 00:00:50,885
LOOKS LIKE YOUR WALK
ON THE BEACH WILL HAVE TO WAIT.

18
00:00:58,433 --> 00:01:03,146
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

19
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:06,233
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

20
00:01:06,274 --> 00:01:10,153
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

21
00:01:10,195 --> 00:01:13,615
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

22
00:01:13,657 --> 00:01:18,245
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

23
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:21,623
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

24
00:01:21,665 --> 00:01:25,627
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

25
00:01:25,669 --> 00:01:28,630
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

26
00:01:28,672 --> 00:01:31,508
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

27
00:01:31,550 --> 00:01:33,802
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

28
00:01:33,844 --> 00:01:37,347
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

29
00:01:37,389 --> 00:01:42,227
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

30
00:01:42,269 --> 00:01:44,605
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

31
00:01:44,646 --> 00:01:49,443
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

32
00:01:49,484 --> 00:01:52,821
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

33
00:01:52,863 --> 00:01:57,701
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

34
00:01:57,743 --> 00:01:59,578
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

35
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:02,122
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

36
00:02:02,163 --> 00:02:06,043
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

37
00:02:06,085 --> 00:02:10,464
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

38
00:02:26,647 --> 00:02:28,107
PLASMA RESIDUE?

39
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:29,733
YOUR WARP INJECTORS
WERE FULL OF IT.

40
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:31,860
OH, I MUST BE MORE DILIGENT
ABOUT ROUTINE MAINTENANCE.

41
00:02:31,902 --> 00:02:34,362
UNLESS YOU ENJOY BEING ADRIFT
IN THE MIDDLE OF NOWHERE.

42
00:02:34,404 --> 00:02:37,699
I'M SORRY TO INCONVENIENCE YOU
WITH SOMETHING THIS TRIVIAL.

43
00:02:37,741 --> 00:02:40,035
BE SURE TO THANK MR. TUCKER
FOR HIS TIME.

44
00:02:40,077 --> 00:02:41,662
HE WANTED ME TO THANK YOU.

45
00:02:41,703 --> 00:02:44,873
IT ISN'T EVERY DAY HE GETS
TO TINKER WITH ALIEN ENGINES.

46
00:02:44,915 --> 00:02:48,502
WE ALSO FOUND A MICROFRACTURE
ON YOUR STARBOARD HULL.

47
00:02:48,543 --> 00:02:50,129
THEY'RE SEALING IT NOW.

48
00:02:50,169 --> 00:02:53,090
-YOUR CREW IS VERY THOROUGH.
-WE WERE GLAD TO HELP.

49
00:02:53,132 --> 00:02:56,802
DO YOU ANSWER EVERY
DISTRESS CALL YOU PICK UP?

50
00:02:56,844 --> 00:02:58,595
IF WE CAN.

51
00:02:58,637 --> 00:03:02,057
THE GALAXY COULD USE
MORE PEOPLE LIKE YOU.

52
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:06,520
TOMORROW --
YOU'LL JOIN ME IN MY HOME!

53
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:08,105
BRING COMMANDER TUCKER.

54
00:03:08,147 --> 00:03:10,107
I'LL PREPARE A MEAL
IN YOUR HONOR.

55
00:03:10,149 --> 00:03:11,817
IT'S THE LEAST I CAN DO
TO SHOW MY GRATITUDE.

56
00:03:11,859 --> 00:03:13,401
THAT'S VERY GENEROUS,

57
00:03:13,443 --> 00:03:15,737
BUT I PROMISED MY CREW
A TRIP TO RISA.

58
00:03:15,779 --> 00:03:18,157
THAT CAN WAIT ONE MORE DAY,
CAN'T IT?

59
00:03:18,197 --> 00:03:21,160
ARCHER: IF I PUT THEM OFF
MUCH LONGER, HEH,

60
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,786
I'M GOING TO HAVE
A MUTINY ON MY HANDS.

61
00:03:22,828 --> 00:03:24,788
THERE'S GOING TO BE
A<i> GESKANA</i> MATCH.

62
00:03:24,830 --> 00:03:26,748
I DOUBT YOU'VE EVER SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE IT.

63
00:03:26,790 --> 00:03:28,792
<i>GESKANA?</i>

64
00:03:28,834 --> 00:03:30,544
YES, YOU MIGHT WANT
TO PARTICIPATE,

65
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:33,338
ASSUMING YOU ENJOY COMPETITION.

66
00:03:33,380 --> 00:03:37,009
I SHOULD WARN YOU, CAPTAIN,

67
00:03:37,051 --> 00:03:39,469
I AM EASILY OFFENDED.

68
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:44,516
-SEND ME THE COORDINATES.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

69
00:03:44,558 --> 00:03:48,269
-I'LL BREAK THE NEWS TO MY CREW.
-DRESS FOR WARM WEATHER.

70
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:00,490
IF IT'S ALL THE SAME
TO YOU, CAPTAIN,

71
00:04:00,532 --> 00:04:01,909
I'LL SIT THIS ONE OUT.

72
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:04,161
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU
TO PASS UP AN AWAY MISSION.

73
00:04:04,203 --> 00:04:06,163
WELL, I'M UP TO MY EARS IN WORK.

74
00:04:06,205 --> 00:04:08,123
THE IMPULSE MANIFOLDS
NEED TO BE PURGED,

75
00:04:08,165 --> 00:04:11,168
THE GRAVITY PLATING ON "C" DECK
STILL ISN'T ALIGNED.

76
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:13,837
-TRIP.
-THE DESERT, SIR?

77
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:17,216
THE HEAT, THE DRY AIR.

78
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:20,052
YOU KNOW HOW
IT SUCKS THE LIFE OUT OF ME.

79
00:04:20,094 --> 00:04:22,721
WHAT ABOUT THE TWO WEEKS
WE SPENT IN AUSTRALIA?

80
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:24,305
WE HAD A GREAT TIME.

81
00:04:24,347 --> 00:04:26,307
TUCKER: SURVIVAL TRAINING
IN THE OUTBACK?

82
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:29,895
DRINKING RECYCLED SWEAT
AND EATING SNAKE MEAT?

83
00:04:29,937 --> 00:04:31,939
THAT'S YOUR IDEA
OF A GREAT TIME?

84
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,899
IT'S NOT GONNA BE LIKE THAT.

85
00:04:33,941 --> 00:04:37,652
I GET THE FEELING ZOBRAL'S A MAN
WHO LIKES TO INDULGE HIS GUESTS.

86
00:04:37,694 --> 00:04:41,115
HE'S PROMISED TO ROLL OUT
THE RED CARPET FOR US.

87
00:04:41,156 --> 00:04:44,284
IT'LL BE MORE FUN
THAN PURGING IMPULSE MANIFOLDS.

88
00:04:46,369 --> 00:04:48,205
ARCHER: WELL, SUIT YOURSELF.

89
00:04:48,247 --> 00:04:50,582
I'LL SEE
IF MALCOLM'S INTERESTED.

90
00:04:50,624 --> 00:04:51,959
BUT I WAS HOPING YOU'D ENJOY

91
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,795
SPENDING SOME TIME
WITH YOUR CAPTAIN.

92
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:57,965
PROMISE WE WON'T HAVE
TO EAT ANY SNAKE MEAT?

93
00:05:22,614 --> 00:05:25,033
IT'S HOTTER THAN HELL OUT THERE.

94
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:27,119
41 DEGREES.

95
00:05:28,411 --> 00:05:30,497
IT'S A DRY HEAT.

96
00:05:39,089 --> 00:05:41,508
ZOBRAL: HA HA! WELCOME!

97
00:05:43,051 --> 00:05:45,679
ARCHER: GOOD TO BE HERE.
YOU REMEMBER COMMANDER TUCKER.

98
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,514
YES!
OF COURSE, OF COURSE.

99
00:05:47,555 --> 00:05:49,474
THIS IS THE MAN
WHO REPAIRED MY SHIP.

100
00:05:49,516 --> 00:05:50,976
A BRILLIANT ENGINEER.

101
00:05:51,018 --> 00:05:53,312
TUCKER: AH, IT WAS JUST
A COUPLE OF CLOGGED INJECTORS.

102
00:05:53,352 --> 00:05:54,688
OH, YOU ARE FAR TOO MODEST.

103
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:55,981
WELL, I HOPE YOU'RE HUNGRY.

104
00:05:56,023 --> 00:05:58,775
I'VE PREPARED QUITE A FEAST.

105
00:06:00,944 --> 00:06:03,571
ARE THERE MANY DESERTS
ON YOUR WORLD?

106
00:06:03,613 --> 00:06:06,741
ARCHER: QUITE A FEW,
BUT NONE AS BIG AS THIS ONE.

107
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:08,702
TUCKER: FROM ORBIT,
YOU'D THINK

108
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:10,745
THE ENTIRE PLANET'S
NOTHING BUT SAND.

109
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:15,500
AH, WELL, WE HAVE A HANDFUL
OF LAKES AND SMALL SEAS.

110
00:06:17,127 --> 00:06:19,129
WHAT ABOUT EARTH?

111
00:06:19,171 --> 00:06:21,589
TWO-THIRDS WATER.

112
00:06:21,631 --> 00:06:23,258
EXTRAORDINARY.

113
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:24,885
MORE WINE?

114
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:26,594
HMM. PLEASE.

115
00:06:27,971 --> 00:06:29,306
WHAT'S THAT CALLED AGAIN?

116
00:06:29,348 --> 00:06:31,058
<i>YALASAT.</i>

117
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:34,769
IT'S MADE FROM A CACTUS THAT
GROWS IN THE NORTHERN FOOTHILLS.

118
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:37,105
HOW IS YOUR ROAST<i> TERACAQ?</i>

119
00:06:37,147 --> 00:06:39,107
ARCHER: IT'S VERY GOOD.

120
00:06:39,149 --> 00:06:41,943
WHEN TRIP AND I DID
OUR SURVIVAL TRAINING --

121
00:06:41,985 --> 00:06:45,780
[ CHUCKLES ] -- IN THE DESERT,
WE NEVER ATE THIS WELL.

122
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:48,158
WE MUST HAVE LOST
ABOUT THREE KILOS

123
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,285
DURING THAT LAST WEEK.

124
00:06:50,327 --> 00:06:52,662
THE HEAT ALWAYS TAKES AWAY
MY APPETITE.

125
00:06:52,704 --> 00:06:54,664
DOESN'T SEEM TO BE
BOTHERING YOU NOW.

126
00:06:54,706 --> 00:06:57,458
[ CHUCKLES ]
I GUESS I'M GETTING ACCLIMATED.

127
00:06:57,500 --> 00:07:01,838
AH. IT MUST BE DIFFICULT
ADJUSTING TO NEW CULTURES.

128
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:04,632
IT'S CHALLENGING
AT TIMES, BUT...

129
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:06,676
THAT'S WHY WE'RE OUT HERE.

130
00:07:06,718 --> 00:07:09,679
DID YOU EVER THINK
OF TURNING BACK?

131
00:07:09,721 --> 00:07:11,723
ONLY ONCE.

132
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:13,141
WE WERE ATTACKED
BY A HOSTILE SPECIES

133
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:15,227
WITH A LOT MORE FIREPOWER
THAN<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

134
00:07:15,269 --> 00:07:19,356
I SET A COURSE BACK TO EARTH
TO UPGRADE OUR WEAPONS.

135
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:24,236
BUT WE ENDED UP HAVING TO DO
THE REPAIRS OURSELVES.

136
00:07:24,278 --> 00:07:26,487
TUCKER: THEY HAVEN'T
BOTHERED US SINCE.

137
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:28,489
SOUNDS LIKE YOU'VE HAD
AN EVENTFUL JOURNEY.

138
00:07:28,531 --> 00:07:31,410
ARCHER: IT'S HAD ITS SHARE
OF SURPRISES. HEH!

139
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:34,788
ZOBRAL: WELL, PERHAPS YOUR VISIT
HERE WILL BE ONE OF THEM.

140
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:41,378
OH! YOU'RE GOING TO ENJOY THIS!

141
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:44,214
ARCHER: OH. LOOKS DELICIOUS.
WHAT IS IT?

142
00:07:44,256 --> 00:07:45,799
BLOOD SOUP.

143
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,759
I DON'T USUALLY EAT THIS WELL,

144
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:51,430
BUT I PROMISED YOUR CAPTAIN
AN EXCEPTIONAL MEAL.

145
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,765
WHAT ARE THESE, UH...

146
00:07:53,807 --> 00:07:55,434
LITTLE CHUNKS?

147
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:58,353
UH, THE ESSENCE OF THE MALE,

148
00:07:58,395 --> 00:08:01,315
CHOPPED AND SEASONED.

149
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:05,860
[ CHUCKLES ]

150
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:24,504
BEAUTIFUL TAPESTRIES.

151
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:25,755
ZOBRAL: THANK YOU.

152
00:08:25,797 --> 00:08:27,548
WHICH ONE DO YOU PREFER?

153
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:29,134
UH...

154
00:08:29,176 --> 00:08:32,053
-MMM.
-WELL...

155
00:08:32,095 --> 00:08:34,014
THAT ONE'S INTERESTING.

156
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:35,265
[ GRUNTS ]
IT'S YOURS!

157
00:08:35,307 --> 00:08:36,724
ARCHER: NO, NO, NO, NO.
I COULDN'T.

158
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:39,186
ZOBRAL: PLEASE,
CONSIDER IT A GIFT.

159
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:40,770
YOU'RE FAR TOO GENEROUS.

160
00:08:40,812 --> 00:08:43,398
BESIDES, I WOULDN'T HAVE
ANY PLACE TO HANG IT.

161
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:47,402
SOMETHING...SMALLER, THEN.

162
00:08:47,444 --> 00:08:49,946
AH.

163
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:54,034
I KNOW<i> YOU</i> WILL APPRECIATE THIS.

164
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:56,370
A SULIBAN MADE IT.

165
00:08:56,411 --> 00:09:00,248
A SULIBAN I MET
SEVERAL YEARS AGO.

166
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:04,919
INTERESTING PEOPLE,
DON'T YOU AGREE?

167
00:09:06,129 --> 00:09:07,547
THANK YOU.

168
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:09,424
[ DISTANT HORN BLOWS ]

169
00:09:09,466 --> 00:09:12,135
AH, THE<i> GESKANA</i> MATCH
IS ABOUT TO BEGIN.

170
00:09:12,177 --> 00:09:14,762
I'M HOPING YOU WILL
HONOR US BY PARTICIPATING.

171
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:18,892
TUCKER: NOW?
I JUST ATE A HALF A<i> TERACAQ.</i>

172
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:20,227
AH, YOU WILL BE GLAD YOU DID.

173
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:23,313
<i>GESKANA</i> REQUIRES
A GREAT DEAL OF STRENGTH.

174
00:09:25,482 --> 00:09:27,025
AH!

175
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,573
[ GRUNTING ]

176
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:53,218
EH!

177
00:09:53,260 --> 00:09:54,635
[ LAUGHTER ]

178
00:09:54,677 --> 00:09:56,012
WOW.

179
00:09:56,054 --> 00:09:58,181
THINK YOU'RE READY?

180
00:09:58,223 --> 00:10:01,017
I'LL GIVE IT A SHOT, CAPTAIN.

181
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:03,895
I CAN'T PROMISE
WE'LL WIN ANY TROPHIES.

182
00:10:03,937 --> 00:10:07,274
THIS IS AN IDEAL GAME
FOR MEN LIKE YOU.

183
00:10:09,943 --> 00:10:11,986
THANKS.

184
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:24,624
[ BEEPS ]

185
00:10:24,665 --> 00:10:26,543
-WE'RE BEING HAILED.
-THE CAPTAIN?

186
00:10:26,585 --> 00:10:30,464
NO, IT'S COMING FROM A CITY
ON THE FAR SIDE OF THE DESERT.

187
00:10:30,505 --> 00:10:32,382
PUT IT THROUGH.

188
00:10:33,841 --> 00:10:36,010
THIS IS<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

189
00:10:36,052 --> 00:10:39,055
<i>SEVERAL HOURS AGO,</i>
<i>YOU LAUNCHED A SMALL VESSEL</i>

190
00:10:39,097 --> 00:10:41,600
<i>TO AN ENCAMPMENT</i>
<i>IN THE CYGNIAI EXPANSE.</i>

191
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:43,351
<i>WOULD YOU TELL ME WHY?</i>

192
00:10:43,393 --> 00:10:46,854
OUR CAPTAIN AND CHIEF ENGINEER
WERE INVITED.

193
00:10:46,896 --> 00:10:49,816
<i>-BY WHOM?</i>
-A MAN NAMED ZOBRAL.

194
00:10:49,857 --> 00:10:51,734
AND YOU ARE?

195
00:10:51,776 --> 00:10:53,278
<i>CHANCELLOR TRELIT.</i>

196
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:56,364
<i>WHY ARE YOU IN CONTACT</i>
<i>WITH THIS MAN?</i>

197
00:10:56,406 --> 00:11:00,243
HIS SHIP WAS DAMAGED,
AND WE ASSISTED HIM.

198
00:11:00,285 --> 00:11:03,497
IN RETURN, HE OFFERED
HIS HOSPITALITY.

199
00:11:03,538 --> 00:11:04,831
<i>HOSPITALITY?</i>

200
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:06,625
<i>I HOPE YOU'RE AWARE</i>
<i>THAT MOST LIKELY,</i>

201
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:09,877
<i>YOU'LL NEVER SEE YOUR CAPTAIN</i>
<i>OR ENGINEER AGAIN.</i>

202
00:11:16,134 --> 00:11:19,095
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING,
GRUNTING ]

203
00:11:26,227 --> 00:11:29,272
-YOU ALL RIGHT?
-NEVER BETTER.

204
00:11:40,158 --> 00:11:41,451
MAN: HERE!

205
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:47,123
SECOND MAN: BLOCK OUT!

206
00:11:48,749 --> 00:11:51,294
MAN: HERE! HERE!

207
00:11:51,336 --> 00:11:53,754
GET IN FRONT OF IT!

208
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:55,882
CUT HIM OFF!

209
00:11:55,923 --> 00:11:58,218
NOW!

210
00:11:58,259 --> 00:11:59,718
OH!

211
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:02,721
[ LAUGHTER ]

212
00:12:06,685 --> 00:12:09,396
-SO CLOSE!
-GOOD SHOT.

213
00:12:10,605 --> 00:12:12,106
NEXT TIME.

214
00:12:12,148 --> 00:12:14,108
TWO CENTIMETERS TO THE RIGHT,
AND YOU WOULD'VE HAD IT.

215
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:16,110
NEXT TIME, I'LL SET YOU UP
WITH A NO-LOOK PASS.

216
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:17,362
ALL RIGHT.

217
00:12:17,404 --> 00:12:18,988
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

218
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:21,074
ZOBRAL: AH! HERE, HERE.

219
00:12:22,492 --> 00:12:23,868
ARCHER.

220
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,412
I need to speak to you, Captain.

221
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:27,622
[ SCOFFS ]
CAN'T IT WAIT?

222
00:12:27,664 --> 00:12:30,083
WE'RE A LITTLE BUSY
AT THE MOMENT.

223
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:32,793
It's urgent.
Are you alone?

224
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:34,337
HOLD ON A MINUTE.

225
00:12:34,379 --> 00:12:36,715
IT'S MY SCIENCE OFFICER.

226
00:12:36,755 --> 00:12:39,593
SHE SAYS IT'S IMPORTANT.
DO YOU MIND?

227
00:12:39,634 --> 00:12:42,596
TAKE YOUR TIME. HEH!

228
00:12:42,637 --> 00:12:44,889
HA HA! CATCH YOUR BREATH.

229
00:12:44,931 --> 00:12:46,182
What's the problem?

230
00:12:46,224 --> 00:12:47,434
I HAVE BEEN CONTACTED BY

231
00:12:47,475 --> 00:12:48,809
A GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL IN A CITY

232
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:51,438
ABOUT 200 KILOMETERS
FROM WHERE YOU ARE NOW.

233
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:54,399
HE CLAIMS THAT YOU'RE IN DANGER.

234
00:12:54,441 --> 00:12:56,025
WHAT KIND OF DANGER?

235
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:57,318
According to him,

236
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,571
ZOBRAL AND HIS MEN
ARE TERRORISTS.

237
00:12:59,613 --> 00:13:01,615
They've been responsible
for numerous attacks

238
00:13:01,656 --> 00:13:04,158
on civilian targets
within the city.

239
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:07,203
MAYBE I'M WRONG, BUT THEY DON'T
SEEM LIKE TERRORISTS TO ME.

240
00:13:07,245 --> 00:13:09,122
PERHAPS NOT.

241
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,790
BUT UNTIL WE'RE CERTAIN
WHO THEY ARE,

242
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:14,586
I SUGGEST YOU RETURN
TO THE SHIP.

243
00:13:20,258 --> 00:13:22,343
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

244
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:28,558
I HOPE EVERYTHING IS ALL RIGHT.

245
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,184
ARCHER: THE PROBLEM WITH BEING
A STARSHIP CAPTAIN IS

246
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:31,770
YOU'RE NEVER REALLY OFF DUTY.

247
00:13:31,810 --> 00:13:34,648
I'M AFRAID WE HAVE TO
CUT OUR VISIT SHORT.

248
00:13:34,689 --> 00:13:36,857
OH, I'M SORRY TO HEAR THAT.

249
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:38,109
WHAT'S GOING ON?

250
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:40,069
PROBLEM WITH
THE STARBOARD ENGINE.

251
00:13:40,111 --> 00:13:42,905
T'POL SAYS SHE NEEDS US
UP THERE RIGHT AWAY.

252
00:13:42,947 --> 00:13:45,032
CAN'T WE AT LEAST
FINISH THIS QUARTER?

253
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:48,911
REMEMBER THOSE IMPULSE MANIFOLDS
YOU SAID NEEDED PURGING?

254
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:50,997
YOU WERE RIGHT.

255
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:55,876
WELL, THANKS
FOR ONE HELL OF A GAME.

256
00:13:55,918 --> 00:13:59,673
YOU MUST HAVE OTHER PEOPLE
THAT CAN CORRECT THIS PROBLEM.

257
00:13:59,714 --> 00:14:01,090
I WISH WE DID.

258
00:14:01,132 --> 00:14:04,302
ZOBRAL: AS I SAID, CAPTAIN,
I AM EASILY OFFENDED.

259
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:07,013
WE'LL COME BACK IF THERE'S TIME.
I PROMISE.

260
00:14:07,054 --> 00:14:11,017
ZOBRAL: YOU SHOULD NOT
BELIEVE THE TOROTHANS!

261
00:14:11,058 --> 00:14:12,644
I HAVE JUST BEEN INFORMED
THAT WE PICKED UP

262
00:14:12,686 --> 00:14:14,688
A LENGTHY TRANSMISSION
BETWEEN YOUR VESSEL

263
00:14:14,729 --> 00:14:16,272
AND CHANCELLOR TRELIT.

264
00:14:16,314 --> 00:14:19,942
WHATEVER HE TOLD YOUR
SCIENCE OFFICER, IT IS NOT TRUE!

265
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:23,863
I WANTED THIS TO WAIT
TILL LATER, BUT I BEG YOU,

266
00:14:23,904 --> 00:14:27,908
LET ME EXPLAIN THE REAL REASON
WHY I ASKED YOU HERE.

267
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:30,119
YOU HAVE A REPUTATION

268
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:33,331
FOR BEING FAIR,
A MAN OF GREAT INTEGRITY.

269
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:35,333
WHEN YOU HEAR WHAT I
HAVE TO SAY,

270
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:38,211
I AM CERTAIN
YOU WILL WANT TO HELP US.

271
00:14:46,260 --> 00:14:49,889
IT IS CALLED A<i> YROTT.</i>

272
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:53,893
THE WORD MEANS "TO STAND APART."

273
00:14:53,934 --> 00:14:55,854
WHEN WE LIVED IN THE CITIES,

274
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:59,982
WE WERE FORCED TO WEAR THESE
WHENEVER WE WALKED IN PUBLIC.

275
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:05,655
ARCHER: I TAKE IT
THOSE DAYS ARE OVER.

276
00:15:07,657 --> 00:15:10,326
WHEN THE CASTE SYSTEM
WAS FINALLY ABOLISHED,

277
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:12,245
WE WERE LED TO BELIEVE
THAT EVERYONE

278
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:14,288
WOULD BE TREATED EQUALLY.

279
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:16,165
I REMEMBER THE CELEBRATIONS --

280
00:15:16,207 --> 00:15:18,835
<i>YROTTS</i> BEING BURNED
IN THE STREETS,

281
00:15:18,877 --> 00:15:23,673
PEOPLE SAYING THAT WE HAD
FINALLY BEEN GRANTED OUR RIGHTS.

282
00:15:23,715 --> 00:15:27,301
THE TOROTHAN CLAN
SIGNED THE ACCORD,

283
00:15:27,343 --> 00:15:29,763
BUT THEY NEVER ABIDED BY IT.

284
00:15:29,804 --> 00:15:32,432
ZOBRAL: THEY STILL CONTROL
THE GOVERNMENT, THE LANDS,

285
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:34,392
THE RESOURCES, EVERYTHING.

286
00:15:34,434 --> 00:15:36,853
WE SPENT 10 YEARS
STAGING PROTESTS,

287
00:15:36,895 --> 00:15:40,189
APPEALING TO THE COURTS,
UNTIL FINALLY WE REALIZED

288
00:15:40,231 --> 00:15:43,777
THERE WAS ONLY ONE WAY
TO GET THEIR ATTENTION.

289
00:15:43,818 --> 00:15:46,613
WE HAVE HUNDREDS OF CAMPS
JUST LIKE THIS ONE

290
00:15:46,654 --> 00:15:48,823
ALL ACROSS THE DESERT,
AND WE ARE GOING TO KEEP

291
00:15:48,865 --> 00:15:52,619
ATTACKING THE TOROTHANS
UNTIL OUR VOICES ARE HEARD.

292
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:55,580
THEY CALL<i> US</i> TERRORISTS,

293
00:15:55,622 --> 00:16:00,167
BUT THE TRUTH IS THEY HAVE BEEN
TERRORIZING<i> US</i> FOR CENTURIES.

294
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:03,755
YOU SAID YOU BROUGHT ME
DOWN HERE FOR A REASON.

295
00:16:03,797 --> 00:16:08,050
I HAVE A FEELING IT WASN'T
TO HEAR A HISTORY LESSON.

296
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:11,178
MMM.

297
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:17,351
THE TOROTHANS HAVE TEN TIMES
AS MANY SOLDIERS AS WE DO.

298
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:22,022
WE WON'T LAST MUCH LONGER
WITHOUT YOUR HELP.

299
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:29,238
I REALLY DON'T SEE
WHAT I CAN DO FOR YOU.

300
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:31,198
[ CHUCKLES ]

301
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,868
THEY SAID YOU WOULD BE HUMBLE.
[ LAUGHS ]

302
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:35,829
I SCANNED YOUR VESSEL.

303
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:40,333
YOU HAVE AN ARSENAL
OF POWERFUL WEAPONS.

304
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:44,712
BUT MORE IMPORTANTLY,
I-I NEED YOUR WISDOM.

305
00:16:44,754 --> 00:16:48,257
OUR CURRENT STRATEGY
ISN'T WORKING.

306
00:16:48,299 --> 00:16:51,093
BUT I-I AM CONFIDENT
THAT TOGETHER,

307
00:16:51,135 --> 00:16:53,053
WE CAN FIND ONE THAT DOES.

308
00:16:56,349 --> 00:17:00,937
I WOULD BE HONORED
TO FIGHT ALONGSIDE YOU,

309
00:17:00,979 --> 00:17:03,105
AS WOULD ALL OF MY MEN.

310
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:04,315
[ DISTANT EXPLOSION ]

311
00:17:04,357 --> 00:17:05,692
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?

312
00:17:05,733 --> 00:17:07,861
TOROTHAN CRUISERS.

313
00:17:07,902 --> 00:17:10,154
USUALLY THEY BEGIN
THEIR BOMBARDMENT AFTER DARK.

314
00:17:10,196 --> 00:17:13,324
THEY'RE GETTING STARTED
EARLY TODAY.

315
00:17:14,784 --> 00:17:16,452
ARCHER: I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'VE HEARD ABOUT ME,

316
00:17:16,494 --> 00:17:17,954
BUT I THINK YOU'VE BEEN MISLED.

317
00:17:17,996 --> 00:17:19,956
-WHAT ABOUT THE SULIBAN?
-WHAT ABOUT THEM?

318
00:17:19,998 --> 00:17:22,000
ZOBRAL: YOU LIBERATED
A DETENTION CAMP,

319
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,584
FREED THOUSANDS OF PRISONERS.

320
00:17:23,626 --> 00:17:25,294
[ DISTANT EXPLOSION ]
WHO TOLD YOU THAT?

321
00:17:25,336 --> 00:17:27,213
A SULIBAN TRANSPORT CAPTAIN.

322
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:30,341
HE TOLD ME OF AN EXPLORER
WHO WAS ALSO A GREAT WARRIOR,

323
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:33,594
A MAN WHO HELPED THEM
DEFEAT AN ENTIRE ARMY--

324
00:17:33,636 --> 00:17:36,723
CAPTAIN JONATHAN ARCHER.

325
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:38,432
MAN: TWO CRUISERS, SIR--
THEY'VE HIT

326
00:17:38,474 --> 00:17:39,684
ONE OF OUR PULSE CANNONS.

327
00:17:39,726 --> 00:17:42,020
AH, PREPARE MY SHIP.

328
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:45,940
THIS WON'T LAST
MORE THAN A FEW HOURS.

329
00:17:45,982 --> 00:17:48,568
WE'LL CONTINUE
THIS DISCUSSION LATER.

330
00:17:48,609 --> 00:17:50,653
YOU'LL BE SAFE HERE.

331
00:17:50,695 --> 00:17:51,905
IF IT'S ALL THE SAME TO YOU,

332
00:17:51,946 --> 00:17:53,489
WE'D RATHER GET BACK
TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

333
00:17:53,531 --> 00:17:54,949
ZOBRAL: WELL,
YOUR SHUTTLE'S THRUSTERS

334
00:17:54,991 --> 00:17:56,534
WOULD DRAW THEIR ATTENTION.

335
00:17:56,576 --> 00:17:58,369
YOU'D BECOME AN EASY TARGET.

336
00:17:58,411 --> 00:17:59,954
ZOBRAL: PLEASE.

337
00:17:59,996 --> 00:18:01,247
I WOULDN'T BE A VERY GOOD HOST

338
00:18:01,288 --> 00:18:03,165
IF I ALLOWED YOU TO GET KILLED.

339
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:07,169
[ DISTANT EXPLOSION ]

340
00:18:16,763 --> 00:18:19,515
THERE'S A NUMBER OF SHIPS
STRAFING THE ENCAMPMENT.

341
00:18:20,725 --> 00:18:22,101
HAIL THE CAPTAIN.

342
00:18:22,142 --> 00:18:24,103
[ BEEPING ]

343
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:26,022
[ STATIC CRACKLING ]

344
00:18:26,064 --> 00:18:28,733
T'POL: CAPTAIN,
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

345
00:18:28,775 --> 00:18:32,152
We've taken shelter...
should be --

346
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:34,154
THAT'S THE BEST I CAN GIVE YOU.

347
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:36,741
THE ENTIRE REGION IS FLOODED
WITH JAMMING SIGNALS.

348
00:18:36,783 --> 00:18:38,826
WELL, WE CAN'T JUST
LEAVE THEM DOWN THERE.

349
00:18:38,868 --> 00:18:40,745
WHAT ABOUT THE TRANSPORTER?

350
00:18:40,787 --> 00:18:43,664
REED: I CAN'T LOCALIZE
THEIR BIO-SIGNS.

351
00:18:43,706 --> 00:18:45,875
I'LL TAKE A SHUTTLEPOD
AND FIND THEM MYSELF.

352
00:18:45,917 --> 00:18:48,044
IN THE MIDDLE OF AN ASSAULT?

353
00:18:51,171 --> 00:18:54,258
SEE IF YOU CAN FIND
CHANCELLOR TRELIT.

354
00:18:56,594 --> 00:18:58,220
ARCHER TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

355
00:18:58,262 --> 00:19:00,222
[ STATIC CRACKLING ]

356
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:01,808
THANKS.

357
00:19:01,849 --> 00:19:03,476
<i>ENTERPRISE.</i>

358
00:19:03,517 --> 00:19:05,103
RESPOND.

359
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:07,187
[ STATIC CRACKLING ]

360
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:10,566
-OH, MAN.
-OH!

361
00:19:10,608 --> 00:19:12,568
-ROUGH GAME.
-[ GROANS ]

362
00:19:12,610 --> 00:19:15,237
THAT DAMN MIDFIELDER
KNOCKED ME DOWN THREE TIMES

363
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:17,156
DURING THE LAST QUARTER.

364
00:19:17,197 --> 00:19:20,827
OH, I MUST'VE BRUISED
HALF A DOZEN RIBS.

365
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:23,830
BETTER HAVE DR. PHLOX TAKE
A LOOK AT IT WHEN WE GET BACK.

366
00:19:24,664 --> 00:19:27,333
[ DISTANT EXPLOSION ]

367
00:19:28,751 --> 00:19:31,253
SO DOES THE...GREAT WARRIOR

368
00:19:31,295 --> 00:19:33,840
HAVE ANY IDEAS ABOUT HOW WE'RE
GETTING OUT OF HERE?

369
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:36,968
[ SIGHS ]

370
00:19:39,804 --> 00:19:42,932
YOU'RE NOT THINKING
ABOUT HELPING THESE PEOPLE?

371
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:48,062
ARCHER: I WAS THINKING
ABOUT THOSE SULIBAN PRISONERS.

372
00:19:48,104 --> 00:19:49,647
[ GRUNTS ]

373
00:19:49,689 --> 00:19:52,232
IF WE HADN'T HELPED THEM ESCAPE,

374
00:19:52,274 --> 00:19:54,986
WE WOULDN'T BE IN
THIS SITUATION.

375
00:19:55,028 --> 00:19:58,114
AH. T'POL'S EARS
MUST BE BURNING.

376
00:19:58,156 --> 00:19:59,740
[ EXPLOSION ]

377
00:19:59,782 --> 00:20:01,826
[ GROANS ]

378
00:20:04,829 --> 00:20:07,498
WANT YOUR
CHIEF ENGINEER'S ADVICE?

379
00:20:07,540 --> 00:20:09,083
WHAT IS IT?

380
00:20:09,125 --> 00:20:11,544
[ SIGHS ]
WALK AWAY.

381
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:13,921
THEY LURED US DOWN HERE
UNDER FALSE PRETENSES,

382
00:20:13,963 --> 00:20:16,924
AND NOW THEY'RE ASKING US
TO HELP THEM FIGHT A WAR?

383
00:20:16,966 --> 00:20:18,384
THAT'S A LOT DIFFERENT
THAN BREAKING

384
00:20:18,425 --> 00:20:20,094
A FEW INNOCENT PEOPLE
OUT OF PRISON.

385
00:20:20,136 --> 00:20:24,098
ARCHER: THERE'S JUST
ONE PROBLEM -- ZOBRAL.

386
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:27,185
I GET THE FEELING HE'S NOT
GONNA TAKE NO FOR AN ANSWER.

387
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:29,478
[ EXPLOSION ]

388
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:38,029
[ SPITS, COUGHING ]

389
00:20:41,949 --> 00:20:43,534
COME ON.

390
00:20:43,576 --> 00:20:45,244
[ COUGHING ]

391
00:20:49,749 --> 00:20:52,001
[ EXPLOSIONS CONTINUE ]

392
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:01,677
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU,

393
00:21:01,719 --> 00:21:03,763
BUT I'D RATHER TAKE MY CHANCES
OUT IN THAT DESERT.

394
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:05,765
THOUGHT YOU HATED THE DESERT.

395
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:07,725
NOT TONIGHT.

396
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:10,477
[ EXPLOSION ]
[ GRUNTS ]

397
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:42,676
YOU NEGLECTED TO MENTION

398
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:44,845
THAT YOU'D BE ATTACKING
THE ENCAMPMENT.

399
00:21:44,887 --> 00:21:47,514
<i>AND YOU ASSURED ME YOUR PEOPLE</i>
<i>WOULD BE LEAVING THE SURFACE.</i>

400
00:21:47,556 --> 00:21:48,975
<i>WHY DIDN'T THEY?</i>

401
00:21:49,016 --> 00:21:51,811
CAPTAIN ARCHER WANTED
TO SPEAK WITH ZOBRAL.

402
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:54,230
<i>INTERESTING.</i>
<i>WHERE ARE THEY NOW?</i>

403
00:21:54,272 --> 00:21:55,856
I DON'T KNOW.

404
00:21:55,898 --> 00:21:58,317
IF YOU'D BE WILLING
TO END YOUR ASSAULT,

405
00:21:58,358 --> 00:22:00,319
WE COULD LAUNCH A SEARCH PARTY.

406
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:01,862
<i>YOU EXPECT US TO STAND BY</i>

407
00:22:01,904 --> 00:22:04,615
<i>WHILE YOU SEND MORE PEOPLE</i>
<i>TO JOIN ZOBRAL?</i>

408
00:22:04,657 --> 00:22:08,286
IF YOU BELIEVE WE'RE ASSISTING
THE TERRORISTS, YOU'RE MISTAKEN.

409
00:22:08,327 --> 00:22:09,703
<i>OF COURSE.</i>
<i>I FORGOT.</i>

410
00:22:09,745 --> 00:22:12,706
<i>THEY JUST WENT DOWN</i>
<i>FOR THE HOSPITALITY.</i>

411
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:16,085
LET US FIND THEM,
AND WE'LL LEAVE IMMEDIATELY.

412
00:22:16,127 --> 00:22:17,920
<i>THAT'S WHAT</i>
<i>YOU PROMISED BEFORE.</i>

413
00:22:17,962 --> 00:22:19,630
<i>WE'LL LOCATE</i>
<i>YOUR MEN OURSELVES</i>

414
00:22:19,672 --> 00:22:21,841
<i>AND DEAL WITH THEM</i>
<i>ACCORDINGLY.</i>

415
00:22:21,882 --> 00:22:24,384
<i>THAT'S ASSUMING THEY HAVEN'T</i>
<i>ALREADY BEEN KILLED.</i>

416
00:22:24,426 --> 00:22:26,179
-CHANCELLOR --
<i>-IF YOU ATTEMPT</i>

417
00:22:26,220 --> 00:22:28,222
<i>TO LAUNCH ANOTHER SHUTTLECRAFT,</i>
<i>WE'LL HAVE NO CHOICE</i>

418
00:22:28,264 --> 00:22:30,724
<i>BUT TO CONSIDER IT</i>
<i>AS AN ENEMY VESSEL.</i>

419
00:22:32,185 --> 00:22:34,187
I'VE LOST SENSOR CONTACT
WITH THE SURFACE.

420
00:22:34,228 --> 00:22:37,815
SOME KIND OF ORBITAL
DISPERSION FIELD.

421
00:22:37,857 --> 00:22:40,358
I CAN'T GET ANY READINGS BELOW
A HUNDRED KILOMETERS.

422
00:22:58,211 --> 00:23:00,129
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

423
00:23:03,381 --> 00:23:05,301
TUCKER: TWO MEN
OUT IN THE OPEN.

424
00:23:05,343 --> 00:23:08,095
YOU'D THINK THEY WOULD HAVE
SPOTTED US BY NOW.

425
00:23:10,014 --> 00:23:12,099
WE'RE DOWN HERE!

426
00:23:15,144 --> 00:23:17,813
ARCHER: YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
YELL A LITTLE LOUDER THAN THAT.

427
00:23:17,855 --> 00:23:19,481
TUCKER: HUH!

428
00:23:19,523 --> 00:23:21,150
[ GRUNTING ]

429
00:23:22,442 --> 00:23:26,488
YOU SURE WE'RE GOING
IN THE RIGHT DIRECTION?

430
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:29,075
ARCHER: IT WAS EAST OF THE CAMP.

431
00:23:29,116 --> 00:23:31,827
WE'RE HEADING EAST.

432
00:23:33,411 --> 00:23:34,621
HOW FAR?

433
00:23:34,663 --> 00:23:36,249
ABOUT 30 KILOMETERS.

434
00:23:36,290 --> 00:23:37,958
30?

435
00:23:39,293 --> 00:23:42,129
WHAT IF WE FIND MORE
OF ZOBRAL'S MEN INSIDE?

436
00:23:42,171 --> 00:23:44,131
ARCHER: IT LOOKED ABANDONED.

437
00:23:44,173 --> 00:23:46,092
[ PANTING ]

438
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:47,843
TUCKER: ALL I SAW WAS SAND.

439
00:23:47,885 --> 00:23:50,637
I DON'T REMEMBER ANY BUILDINGS.

440
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:53,682
ARCHER: THAT'S BECAUSE YOU
FORGOT YOUR SURVIVAL TRAINING.

441
00:23:53,724 --> 00:23:58,271
TAKE A GOOD LOOK ON YOUR WAY IN
AT YOUR SURROUNDINGS.

442
00:23:58,312 --> 00:24:01,357
TUCKER: DIDN'T THEY
ALSO SAY SOMETHING

443
00:24:01,399 --> 00:24:04,526
ABOUT ONLY WALKING AT NIGHT?

444
00:24:04,568 --> 00:24:06,444
OHH.

445
00:24:06,486 --> 00:24:10,157
CAN'T WE WAIT
UNTIL IT COOLS DOWN A LITTLE?

446
00:24:10,199 --> 00:24:12,534
THAT COULD BE FOR ANOTHER...

447
00:24:12,576 --> 00:24:15,246
[ SIGHS ]
EIGHT OR NINE HOURS.

448
00:24:15,288 --> 00:24:17,248
WE NEED TO FIND SHELTER.

449
00:24:17,290 --> 00:24:19,250
20 MINUTES, CAPTAIN.

450
00:24:19,292 --> 00:24:20,667
TRIP.

451
00:24:20,709 --> 00:24:23,296
OH.

452
00:24:23,337 --> 00:24:25,589
10?

453
00:24:31,469 --> 00:24:33,513
[ GROANS ]

454
00:24:38,269 --> 00:24:41,147
TO CHERRY-FLAVORED SNOW CONES.

455
00:24:41,188 --> 00:24:45,318
WHAT I WOULDN'T GIVE FOR ONE
RIGHT ABOUT NOW.

456
00:24:56,078 --> 00:24:57,663
OH.

457
00:24:57,704 --> 00:25:00,166
[ DISTANT RUMBLING ]

458
00:25:00,207 --> 00:25:02,126
YOU HEAR THAT?

459
00:25:02,168 --> 00:25:03,585
WHAT?

460
00:25:03,627 --> 00:25:06,172
SOUNDS LIKE A SHIP.

461
00:25:07,547 --> 00:25:10,176
THINK THE HEAT'S
GETTING TO YOU.

462
00:25:10,217 --> 00:25:11,427
NO.

463
00:25:11,469 --> 00:25:13,429
LISTEN.

464
00:25:13,471 --> 00:25:16,140
[ WHIRRING IN DISTANCE ]

465
00:25:17,515 --> 00:25:20,102
OVER THERE.

466
00:25:20,144 --> 00:25:22,480
A SHUTTLEPOD?

467
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:24,564
NO.

468
00:25:26,150 --> 00:25:28,819
SOMETHING A LOT BIGGER.

469
00:25:39,121 --> 00:25:41,207
[ COUGHS ]

470
00:25:52,218 --> 00:25:53,386
[ COUGHS ]

471
00:25:53,427 --> 00:25:56,389
-YOU ALL RIGHT?
-YEAH.

472
00:25:56,430 --> 00:25:59,016
REED: A DISPERSION FIELD
COVERS HALF THE CONTINENT.

473
00:25:59,058 --> 00:26:01,227
BUT IF I DISABLE
THESE THREE SATELLITES,

474
00:26:01,268 --> 00:26:04,230
I THINK I CAN GET A CLEAR
READING OF THE EASTERN DESERT.

475
00:26:04,271 --> 00:26:06,232
THAT MIGHT PROVOKE
THE TOROTHANS.

476
00:26:06,273 --> 00:26:08,901
I SUGGEST YOU TRY TO FIND
A LESS INTRUSIVE WAY

477
00:26:08,942 --> 00:26:11,611
TO PENETRATE THEIR DEFENSES.

478
00:26:13,655 --> 00:26:15,615
WHY MONTANA?

479
00:26:15,657 --> 00:26:18,285
OF ALL THE PLACES THE VULCANS
COULD HAVE LANDED,

480
00:26:18,327 --> 00:26:20,578
THEY CHOSE BOZEMAN, MONTANA.

481
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:23,457
HUMANITY'S FIRST WARP DRIVE
WAS DEVELOPED THERE.

482
00:26:23,499 --> 00:26:25,084
IT SEEMED A LOGICAL PLACE
TO BEGIN.

483
00:26:25,125 --> 00:26:28,379
WELL, HOW DID THEY KNOW IT
WOULDN'T ALARM OTHER NATIONS?

484
00:26:28,421 --> 00:26:31,340
AN ALIEN SPECIES MAKES CONTACT
WITH THE UNITED STATES.

485
00:26:31,382 --> 00:26:33,717
COULD HAVE MADE A LOT
OF OTHER COUNTRIES NERVOUS.

486
00:26:33,759 --> 00:26:35,677
WHAT'S YOUR POINT?

487
00:26:35,719 --> 00:26:39,348
IT SEEMS TO ME THAT WE'RE GONNA
RUN INTO SIMILAR PROBLEMS.

488
00:26:39,390 --> 00:26:41,725
WE GET INVITED TO DINNER,
AND BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,

489
00:26:41,767 --> 00:26:44,311
WE'RE ACCUSED
OF TAKING SIDES IN A WAR.

490
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:51,068
CONTACTING NEW WORLDS ALWAYS
INVOLVES UNEXPECTED RISKS.

491
00:26:51,110 --> 00:26:54,113
THE HIGH COMMAND HAS
VERY SPECIFIC PROTOCOLS

492
00:26:54,154 --> 00:26:57,032
REGARDING PLANETARY CONFLICTS.

493
00:26:57,074 --> 00:26:59,285
EVENTUALLY, CAPTAIN ARCHER
WILL HAVE TO

494
00:26:59,326 --> 00:27:02,913
CREATE SOME DIRECTIVES
OF HIS OWN.

495
00:27:37,573 --> 00:27:39,492
COME ON. COME ON.

496
00:27:39,533 --> 00:27:43,162
WE GOT TO KEEP MOVING.
COME ON.

497
00:27:44,497 --> 00:27:46,957
MY SHIFT DOESN'T BEGIN
FOR ANOTHER SIX HOURS.

498
00:27:46,999 --> 00:27:48,501
HEY...

499
00:27:48,542 --> 00:27:50,544
WE'RE ALMOST THERE.

500
00:27:50,586 --> 00:27:52,212
WHERE?

501
00:27:52,254 --> 00:27:54,590
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

502
00:27:55,591 --> 00:27:58,511
NICE LITTLE PLACE I KNOW.

503
00:27:58,552 --> 00:28:00,220
PLENTY OF SHADE.

504
00:28:00,262 --> 00:28:02,473
ARE THERE BLANKETS DOWN THERE?

505
00:28:02,515 --> 00:28:05,267
-HUH?
-I'M FREEZING.

506
00:28:07,769 --> 00:28:09,687
HEAT EXHAUSTION.

507
00:28:09,729 --> 00:28:12,441
-[ GRUNTS ]
-COME HERE.

508
00:28:16,069 --> 00:28:18,322
HERE.
THERE YOU GO.

509
00:28:18,364 --> 00:28:20,491
EASY, EASY.

510
00:28:28,499 --> 00:28:30,959
TAKE MINE. GO AHEAD.

511
00:28:31,001 --> 00:28:34,712
NO, SIR. I WON'T TAKE
ANOTHER MAN'S WATER.

512
00:28:34,754 --> 00:28:36,965
YOU DRINK IT.
THAT'S AN ORDER.

513
00:28:37,007 --> 00:28:39,926
[ GROANS ]
GOT TO KEEP MOVING.

514
00:28:39,968 --> 00:28:41,970
TAKE THE WATER
OR I'LL KNOCK YOU

515
00:28:42,012 --> 00:28:44,557
ON YOUR ASS AND POUR IT
DOWN YOUR THROAT.

516
00:28:48,394 --> 00:28:49,936
EASY.

517
00:28:57,611 --> 00:28:58,945
THANKS.

518
00:29:02,908 --> 00:29:04,493
OH!

519
00:29:04,535 --> 00:29:06,203
[ GRUNTS ]

520
00:29:14,127 --> 00:29:16,338
THERE'S A VESSEL APPROACHING
FROM THE SURFACE.

521
00:29:16,380 --> 00:29:17,923
IT'S ZOBRAL.

522
00:29:17,964 --> 00:29:20,300
-[ BEEPS ]
-HE'S HAILING US.

523
00:29:21,968 --> 00:29:24,137
Open your launch doors.
Quickly!

524
00:29:24,179 --> 00:29:26,682
IS THE CAPTAIN WITH YOU?
COMMANDER TUCKER?

525
00:29:26,724 --> 00:29:29,268
No, no,
I'll explain once I'm aboard.

526
00:29:29,309 --> 00:29:30,852
WHERE ARE THEY?

527
00:29:30,894 --> 00:29:32,438
If I'm not in your docking bay

528
00:29:32,479 --> 00:29:35,524
in the next 30 seconds,
I'll be detected.

529
00:29:35,566 --> 00:29:38,277
They'll destroy my ship.

530
00:29:39,486 --> 00:29:41,530
BRING HIM IN.

531
00:29:42,989 --> 00:29:45,451
<i>-HOW</i> MANY?
-THERE WERE 89.

532
00:29:45,492 --> 00:29:48,454
THERE WERE ONLY 89 SULIBAN,
NOT THOUSANDS.

533
00:29:48,495 --> 00:29:51,081
ZOBRAL: MMM.
AND THE ARMY YOU DEFEATED?

534
00:29:51,123 --> 00:29:52,374
REED: I WOULD HARDLY
CALL IT AN ARMY.

535
00:29:52,416 --> 00:29:53,959
IT WAS MORE LIKE
A FEW DOZEN PRISON GUARDS.

536
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:57,170
AND TO BE HONEST, THEY DIDN'T
PUT UP MUCH OF A FIGHT.

537
00:29:57,212 --> 00:30:00,799
T'POL: JONATHAN ARCHER IS
AN EXCELLENT STARSHIP CAPTAIN,

538
00:30:00,840 --> 00:30:04,470
BUT HE'S HARDLY THE INVINCIBLE
WARRIOR DESCRIBED TO YOU.

539
00:30:04,511 --> 00:30:09,057
HMM. WHAT ABOUT HIS
LEGENDARY DESERT TACTICS?

540
00:30:09,099 --> 00:30:11,893
ACTUALLY, I'M THE TACTICAL
OFFICER ON THIS SHIP,

541
00:30:11,935 --> 00:30:15,689
AND I DON'T HAVE ANY EXPERIENCE
AT WAGING DESERT WARFARE.

542
00:30:15,731 --> 00:30:19,401
I'M AFRAID YOU'VE COME
TO THE WRONG PEOPLE FOR HELP.

543
00:30:19,443 --> 00:30:23,113
MMM, ALL THIS FOR NOTHING.

544
00:30:23,155 --> 00:30:24,823
WHAT ABOUT OUR PEOPLE?

545
00:30:24,864 --> 00:30:27,451
WELL, YOU HAVE FAR BETTER
SENSORS THAN WE DO.

546
00:30:27,493 --> 00:30:28,827
I'M SURE YOU'LL FIND THEM.

547
00:30:28,868 --> 00:30:31,288
T'POL: OUR SENSORS ARE
BEING DISRUPTED,

548
00:30:31,330 --> 00:30:33,332
AND THE TOROTHANS HAVE
THREATENED TO FIRE ON US

549
00:30:33,373 --> 00:30:34,916
IF WE LAUNCH A SHUTTLEPOD.

550
00:30:34,958 --> 00:30:37,503
HOW DID YOU GET HERE
WITHOUT THEM SEEING YOU?

551
00:30:37,544 --> 00:30:41,173
THERE IS A NARROW GAP
IN THEIR ORBITAL DETECTION GRID.

552
00:30:41,214 --> 00:30:43,133
IT OCCURS ONCE EVERY 46 MINUTES,

553
00:30:43,175 --> 00:30:46,219
BUT IT IS ONLY OPEN
FOR LESS THAN ONE MINUTE.

554
00:30:46,261 --> 00:30:47,638
I'LL NEED ALL
THE PERTINENT DATA.

555
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,931
ZOBRAL: HA!
YOU'LL NEED MORE THAN THAT!

556
00:30:49,973 --> 00:30:51,600
THE MANEUVERS
ARE EXTREMELY DIFFICULT.

557
00:30:51,642 --> 00:30:53,268
IT TOOK US YEARS TO LEARN THEM.

558
00:30:53,310 --> 00:30:56,396
I'M A QUICK STUDY.

559
00:30:56,438 --> 00:31:00,275
YOU WILL BE SHOT DOWN
BEFORE YOU REACH THE ATMOSPHERE.

560
00:31:00,317 --> 00:31:02,444
WITH YOU AT THE HELM,
OUR CHANCES WOULD IMPROVE.

561
00:31:02,486 --> 00:31:05,447
ZOBRAL: I DON'T HAVE TIME!
MY MEN ARE WAITING FOR ME!

562
00:31:05,489 --> 00:31:07,449
REED: THEN THEY'LL HAVE
TO WAIT A LITTLE LONGER.

563
00:31:07,491 --> 00:31:09,868
YOU'RE THE ONE THAT GOT
OUR PEOPLE STRANDED DOWN THERE.

564
00:31:09,909 --> 00:31:12,954
THEY ARE NOT MY RESPONSIBILITY!

565
00:31:14,707 --> 00:31:17,167
T'POL: YOU'RE MISTAKEN.

566
00:31:18,544 --> 00:31:21,672
THE TOROTHANS BELIEVE
WE'VE JOINED YOUR CAUSE.

567
00:31:22,964 --> 00:31:24,508
IF CAPTAIN ARCHER
AND COMMANDER TUCKER

568
00:31:24,550 --> 00:31:26,552
ARE APPREHENDED,
THEY'LL UNDOUBTEDLY

569
00:31:26,593 --> 00:31:28,721
BE TREATED AS MEMBERS
OF YOUR CLAN.

570
00:31:28,762 --> 00:31:30,723
THEY'LL BECOME VICTIMS
OF THE SAME OPPRESSION

571
00:31:30,764 --> 00:31:33,392
YOU'VE BEEN FIGHTING
ALL THESE YEARS.

572
00:31:33,433 --> 00:31:36,269
YOU SHOULD FEEL AS RESPONSIBLE
FOR THOSE TWO MEN

573
00:31:36,311 --> 00:31:38,647
AS YOU DO FOR YOUR OWN.

574
00:31:41,066 --> 00:31:43,109
[ PANTING ]

575
00:31:57,040 --> 00:31:59,084
OH.

576
00:32:04,798 --> 00:32:07,300
[ GRUNTING ]

577
00:32:25,861 --> 00:32:27,905
EASY.

578
00:32:33,285 --> 00:32:35,328
HOME SWEET HOME.

579
00:33:03,148 --> 00:33:05,066
AH! HA!

580
00:33:05,108 --> 00:33:09,780
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT PLANNING
TO HOG THAT ALL FOR YOURSELF.

581
00:33:09,822 --> 00:33:11,156
HA!

582
00:33:11,197 --> 00:33:12,532
[ SNIFFS ]

583
00:33:16,286 --> 00:33:18,288
WATER'S OFF THE MENU.

584
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:21,374
OH...OH.

585
00:33:31,927 --> 00:33:34,513
NOW, THIS...

586
00:33:34,554 --> 00:33:37,599
IS MY IDEA OF A GREAT TIME.

587
00:33:47,609 --> 00:33:50,236
WHAT'D YOU DO...

588
00:33:50,278 --> 00:33:53,824
RUB...TWO STICKS TOGETHER?

589
00:33:53,866 --> 00:33:57,953
ARCHER: I FOUND A NEW USE
FOR THE STUN SETTING.

590
00:34:00,246 --> 00:34:02,833
IT MAY NOT TASTE
TOO GOOD, BUT...

591
00:34:02,875 --> 00:34:06,085
I THINK I BOILED AWAY ANYTHING
THAT CAN HURT US.

592
00:34:06,127 --> 00:34:08,046
NO, THANKS.

593
00:34:08,087 --> 00:34:10,632
I'M NOT THIRSTY.

594
00:34:10,674 --> 00:34:13,426
LET'S NOT GET INTO
THAT ARGUMENT AGAIN.

595
00:34:23,186 --> 00:34:25,104
WORSE THAN BLOOD SOUP.

596
00:34:25,146 --> 00:34:27,774
-YOU NEED WATER.
-[ SIGHS ]

597
00:34:27,816 --> 00:34:30,402
WHAT I NEED...

598
00:34:30,443 --> 00:34:32,320
IS SLEEP.

599
00:34:32,362 --> 00:34:36,366
YOU GOT A FEVER, TRIP.
YOUR HEART'S RACING.

600
00:34:36,408 --> 00:34:39,369
YOU GOT ALL
THE SYMPTOMS OF HEATSTROKE.

601
00:34:39,411 --> 00:34:41,872
IF YOU FALL ASLEEP,
YOU COULD LAPSE INTO A COMA.

602
00:34:41,914 --> 00:34:43,957
A COMA?

603
00:34:45,918 --> 00:34:47,753
THAT SOUNDS NICE.

604
00:34:47,794 --> 00:34:51,840
WHEN WE GET BACK TO<i> ENTERPRISE,</i>
YOU CAN SLEEP ALL YOU WANT,

605
00:34:51,882 --> 00:34:54,885
BUT RIGHT NOW,
YOU GOT TO STAY WITH ME

606
00:34:54,927 --> 00:34:57,596
AND DRINK THIS WATER.

607
00:34:57,637 --> 00:34:59,890
IF I HAD A NEEDLE, I'D GIVE IT
TO YOU INTRAVENOUSLY,

608
00:34:59,932 --> 00:35:01,975
BUT I DON'T.

609
00:35:02,017 --> 00:35:04,686
COME ON. SIT UP.

610
00:35:06,563 --> 00:35:08,565
THERE YOU GO.

611
00:35:15,447 --> 00:35:17,198
GOOD.

612
00:35:20,911 --> 00:35:22,328
[ COUGHING ]

613
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:31,630
YEAH.

614
00:35:35,926 --> 00:35:37,510
COMMANDER.

615
00:35:39,178 --> 00:35:41,222
AYE, CAPTAIN.

616
00:35:43,182 --> 00:35:45,351
THE WARP REACTOR...

617
00:35:46,937 --> 00:35:49,272
BREAK IT DOWN FOR ME.

618
00:35:51,441 --> 00:35:53,359
WHAT?

619
00:35:53,401 --> 00:35:56,404
WHAT ARE THE EIGHT
MAJOR COMPONENTS?

620
00:35:56,446 --> 00:35:59,365
YOU GOT TO BE KIDDING ME.

621
00:36:00,533 --> 00:36:02,368
NAME THEM.

622
00:36:03,578 --> 00:36:05,664
THAT'S AN ORDER.

623
00:36:08,458 --> 00:36:10,335
WELL...

624
00:36:12,087 --> 00:36:14,547
THERE'S THE DRUMSTICKS...

625
00:36:15,924 --> 00:36:17,634
THIGHS...

626
00:36:18,927 --> 00:36:21,513
WINGS.

627
00:36:21,554 --> 00:36:24,474
YOU GOT ANYTHING TO EAT
AROUND HERE?

628
00:36:24,516 --> 00:36:26,184
NOT AT THE MOMENT.

629
00:36:26,225 --> 00:36:28,145
BUT WHEN WE GET BACK
TO<i> ENTERPRISE,</i>

630
00:36:28,186 --> 00:36:32,524
I'LL HAVE CHEF MAKE YOU A DINNER
YOU'LL NEVER FORGET.

631
00:36:32,565 --> 00:36:36,820
WHAT WOULD YOU LIKE?
ANYTHING.

632
00:36:36,862 --> 00:36:38,738
NOT SNAKE MEAT.

633
00:36:38,780 --> 00:36:42,993
NO, CHEF DOESN'T DO SNAKE
VERY WELL.

634
00:36:44,327 --> 00:36:46,579
TELL ME WHAT YOU WANT.

635
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:49,916
PRIME RIB.

636
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:52,377
OKAY. WHAT ELSE?

637
00:36:53,252 --> 00:36:55,630
MASHED POTATOES

638
00:36:55,672 --> 00:36:59,134
WITH M-MUSHROOM GRAVY.

639
00:36:59,176 --> 00:37:03,596
THE -- THE KIND HE MAKES
ON WEDNESDAY NIGHTS.

640
00:37:03,638 --> 00:37:05,306
NO PROBLEM.

641
00:37:06,641 --> 00:37:08,727
WHAT KIND OF VEGETABLES?

642
00:37:10,687 --> 00:37:13,815
HEY. VEGETABLES?

643
00:37:13,857 --> 00:37:16,943
-BROCCOLI.
-AH.

644
00:37:20,405 --> 00:37:22,323
DESSERT?

645
00:37:23,867 --> 00:37:26,745
-PECAN PIE.
-AH.

646
00:37:36,337 --> 00:37:38,506
TAKE ANOTHER PASS OVER
THE EASTERN BASIN.

647
00:37:38,548 --> 00:37:40,466
OUR SENSORS
WOULD HAVE DETECTED THEM.

648
00:37:40,508 --> 00:37:42,135
NO, THERE'S MAGNETIC DEPOSITS
BELOW THAT BASIN.

649
00:37:42,177 --> 00:37:44,137
THEY COULD BE MASKING
THEIR BIO-SIGNS.

650
00:37:44,179 --> 00:37:47,140
IF WE INCREASED OUR ALTITUDE,
THIS WOULD GO A LOT FASTER.

651
00:37:47,182 --> 00:37:49,893
WE WOULD ALSO RISK
BEING DETECTED.

652
00:38:04,616 --> 00:38:06,576
GEOGRAPHY.

653
00:38:06,618 --> 00:38:08,620
DO YOU KNOW HOW TO PLAY?

654
00:38:09,579 --> 00:38:11,456
GEOGRAPHY?

655
00:38:11,497 --> 00:38:15,710
YOU KNOW,
YOU SAY "AMAZON RIVER,"

656
00:38:15,752 --> 00:38:17,712
WHICH ENDS IN AN "R,"

657
00:38:17,754 --> 00:38:20,006
AND THEN I SAY "RHODE ISLAND."

658
00:38:20,048 --> 00:38:23,635
W-WE'RE GOING TO RHODE ISLAND?

659
00:38:23,676 --> 00:38:25,595
NO.

660
00:38:25,637 --> 00:38:28,431
NO, I-IT'S A GAME.

661
00:38:28,473 --> 00:38:31,143
YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO TELL ME SOME PLACE

662
00:38:31,184 --> 00:38:33,352
THAT STARTS WITH A "D."

663
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:36,022
[ SIGHS ]
OH.

664
00:38:36,064 --> 00:38:38,650
"D."

665
00:38:38,691 --> 00:38:41,360
UH...

666
00:38:42,988 --> 00:38:44,405
DRAYLAX.

667
00:38:44,447 --> 00:38:46,407
"X"?

668
00:38:46,449 --> 00:38:48,576
"X..."

669
00:38:48,618 --> 00:38:49,786
THERE'S ALWAYS --

670
00:38:49,828 --> 00:38:51,663
NO, NO.
NO, DON'T TELL ME.

671
00:38:51,704 --> 00:38:53,665
I KNOW AN "X."

672
00:38:53,706 --> 00:38:55,125
[ SCOFFS ]

673
00:38:55,167 --> 00:38:56,876
XANADU.

674
00:38:56,918 --> 00:38:58,461
[ CHUCKLES ]

675
00:38:58,503 --> 00:39:00,046
THAT'S NOT A REAL PLACE.

676
00:39:00,088 --> 00:39:02,841
-IT DOESN'T MATTER.
-AH, OF COURSE IT MATTERS.

677
00:39:02,882 --> 00:39:05,343
ARCHER: YOU JUST USED
AN ALIEN PLANET -- DRAYLAX.

678
00:39:05,384 --> 00:39:07,929
[ COUGHING ]

679
00:39:07,971 --> 00:39:10,890
EASY. EASY.
HERE.

680
00:39:10,932 --> 00:39:13,893
EASY, EASY.

681
00:39:13,935 --> 00:39:16,896
[ DISTANT EXPLOSION ]

682
00:39:16,938 --> 00:39:18,982
[ EXPLOSION ]

683
00:39:20,900 --> 00:39:23,069
ALL RIGHT.
WHATEVER YOU SAY.

684
00:39:23,111 --> 00:39:25,697
XANADU'S FINE.

685
00:39:34,247 --> 00:39:35,540
GET YOUR HEAD DOWN!

686
00:39:35,581 --> 00:39:37,209
-WHAT?
-GET DOWN!

687
00:39:46,634 --> 00:39:48,678
[ COUGHING ]

688
00:39:51,181 --> 00:39:52,891
WE GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE!

689
00:39:52,932 --> 00:39:54,559
COME ON.

690
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:56,769
[ GROANS ]

691
00:39:58,855 --> 00:40:00,899
I'M PICKING UP WEAPONS FIRE
ON THE SURFACE.

692
00:40:00,940 --> 00:40:02,901
19 KILOMETERS DUE SOUTH.

693
00:40:02,942 --> 00:40:04,527
A TOROTHAN MORTAR.

694
00:40:04,569 --> 00:40:06,445
WOULD THEY BE TARGETING
ONE OF YOUR SETTLEMENTS?

695
00:40:06,487 --> 00:40:08,573
ZOBRAL: WE DON'T HAVE
ANY NEAR THERE.

696
00:40:10,867 --> 00:40:13,161
SET A COURSE
AND PREPARE TO FIRE.

697
00:40:15,038 --> 00:40:18,166
I BELIEVE THEY'VE LOCATED THE
CAPTAIN AND COMMANDER TUCKER.

698
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:39,271
COME ON.

699
00:40:39,312 --> 00:40:42,148
-COME ON.
-[ GROANS ]

700
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:44,859
[ BEEPING ]
I'VE GOT A LOCK.

701
00:40:44,901 --> 00:40:46,611
FIRE.

702
00:40:52,242 --> 00:40:54,202
I SEE THEM.

703
00:40:54,244 --> 00:40:55,828
TWO HUMANS.

704
00:40:55,870 --> 00:40:58,623
BEARING 115, MARK 3.

705
00:40:59,832 --> 00:41:02,127
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

706
00:41:06,798 --> 00:41:09,384
TUCKER: I'M JUST
SLOWING YOU DOWN. GO!

707
00:41:09,426 --> 00:41:12,053
ARCHER: I DON'T REMEMBER
TAKING ORDERS FROM YOU.

708
00:41:23,022 --> 00:41:25,066
[ GRUNTING ]

709
00:42:05,648 --> 00:42:07,650
MY LAUNCH WINDOW OPENS
IN NINE MINUTES.

710
00:42:07,692 --> 00:42:09,610
I SHOULD BE GOING.

711
00:42:09,652 --> 00:42:13,198
I HOPE COMMANDER TUCKER
IS GOING TO BE ALL RIGHT.

712
00:42:13,239 --> 00:42:17,243
I DOUBT I'LL EVER CONVINCE HIM
TO SET FOOT ON ANOTHER DESERT,

713
00:42:17,285 --> 00:42:20,038
BUT...HE'LL BE FINE.

714
00:42:21,498 --> 00:42:26,211
ZOBRAL, EVEN IF I WERE
THE WARRIOR YOU THOUGHT I WAS...

715
00:42:27,628 --> 00:42:30,131
THAT'S NOT WHY
WE'RE OUT HERE.

716
00:42:33,092 --> 00:42:35,136
CAPTAIN.

717
00:42:36,388 --> 00:42:39,057
ZOBRAL: SUBCOMMANDER.

718
00:43:00,703 --> 00:43:03,248
WHAT YOU TOLD HIM WAS CORRECT.

719
00:43:03,289 --> 00:43:06,042
DECISIONS TO GET INVOLVED
IN THE CONFLICTS OF OTHER WORLDS

720
00:43:06,084 --> 00:43:09,087
SHOULD BE LEFT TO GOVERNMENTS,
NOT STARSHIP CAPTAINS.

721
00:43:09,128 --> 00:43:11,089
I KNOW.

722
00:43:11,130 --> 00:43:13,674
THE IRONY IS I HAVE THE FEELING

723
00:43:13,716 --> 00:43:16,761
HIS CAUSE IS WORTH FIGHTING FOR.
